com.swirl

Class NearbyManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.swirl.Manager
      • com.swirl.NearbyManager

  • public class NearbyManager
extends Manager
    The NearbyManager uses the Nearby APIs to scan for beacons registered using the google beacon platform. The Nearby APIs return messages attached to beacons with many types. The NearbyManager handles these attachements in different ways.

    If the Eddystone-UID namespaces are requested to be scanned, then for every Eddystone-UID message (type MESSAGE_TYPE_EDDYSTONE_UID) delivered, the NearbyManager will convert it to a corresponding Eddystone BeaconAdvertisement and broadcast that on the event bus. If the message namespace is MESSAGE_TYPE_SWIRL, the NearbyManager will convert the message to a BeaconAdvertisement using the beacon identity contained in the attchement. Finally, for all other attachment types, a NearbyMessage will be broadcast on the bus with the type and content information contained. A convenience method on SwirlListener: protected void onNearbyMessage(NearbyManager manager, String namespace, String type, byte[] content, int rssi) can be overridden to get notified when those messages arrive.

    • Field Detail

      • MESSAGE_TYPE_SWIRL

        public static final java.lang.String MESSAGE_TYPE_SWIRL
        The type string assigned to default 'swirl' attachements. These attachements are added to beacons in the google beacon platform when registered through the swirl platform. These attachments allow swirl content to be served, when using Nearby for beacon detection.
